&quot;There is no good or evil, there is only power&quot;</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vladius>Vladius</A> at: 6/26/03 5:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naeanthesorcerer>NaeanTheSorcerer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 6:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No MQ?</span><hr size=1> if you use the invis trick for the turnins, an MQ works...i got mine that way.  yes it's true that MQ is not supported, and a guild wizard ended up losing two of his staffs and GM wouldn't help him.  despite this, there are some cool GMs that will at least reimburse the staffs that you had in your possession. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=492380" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://filebox.vt.edu/users/jomarti8/signature.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=malakriss>Malakriss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 324<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 7:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No MQ?</span><hr size=1> For most quests an equal faction level is required.  The wizard epic is one of them.  In order to avoid this just use the invis trick and you'll have no problem.  I've personally done it at least 5 times with no problems.  However if you do botch it, the GMs will tell you to suck a lemon because they don't wish to be helpful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13534<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 7:37 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No MQ?</span><hr size=1> If you lose your MQed staffs, the ones YOU had on you will be reimbursed -- just don't say that you were MQing. They'll pull up the records and see that, yep, you turned in those two objects to the NPC, and will give them back.<br>
<br>
But inviz trick works. I know about a dozen wizards on Vaz, including myself, who got theirs this way. <p><a href="http://www.EQPixelArmy.com" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-animated-banner-animation.gif" height="120" width="80" alt="EQPA" border=0></a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41790" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-animated-banner-text.gif" height=120 width=272 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zertez>zertez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 194<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 8:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No MQ?</span><hr size=1>  SOE has become a little more softer on their stance of MQ in general but most of the time MQ's have been try at your own risk. Verants policy use to be no reimbursement or help with epics in general, if you lost a piece tough luck. <br>
<br>
 I would do what Whiz recommend, if you petition for long enough they will return the staves you had. I would recommend using the invis trick anytime you are doing a MQ, it takes a little more effort but it is not much at all compared to the risk of losing everything. Why risk it when you can use the invis trick almost as easy as a regular trade. Learn from it and do not cut corners if something is important to you and losing it is going to set you back. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=27088.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=27088.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=27088.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=27088.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=27088.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=27088.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email not